description:
&lt;p&gt;NDCAMHS works with children and young people aged 0-18 who have severe to profound hearing loss, have D/deaf parents or have British Sign Language as a first language, and experience emotional and/or behavioural issues. We work to improve the mental health of these children and young people through supporting them and their families, and through working with wider systems such as education and social services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an experienced, motivated mental health practitioner to join our Newcastle outreach team, which covers Carlisle, Northumberland, Teeside, Tyne &amp; Wear . The post holder will make a significant contribution to the outreach service and work within a bi-lingual, bi-cultural multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post provides the opportunity to hold a varied caseload, work flexibly across pathways of care in a variety of community settings and to work closely with clinicians/practitioners in multi-disciplinary teams including Deaf and hearing staff and BSL/English Interpreters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work autonomously, as well as being an effective member of the multidisciplinary team. Excellent problem-solving, communication and interpersonal skills and a positive attitude towards working with deaf children, and their families, with complex mental health needs are essential. You must also be willing to learn British Sign Language skills- training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At present, due to COVID-19, we are offering a remote service via the internet, however when functioning normally, the post holder will be required to travel to a range of settings throughout the North East of England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to express an interest in the above post / would like to discuss it further, please contact Amy Hawkins 07980 967204 or Julie Foster-Goodman 07980 956992&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that the interviews will be held on Thursday 3rd December remotely via Zoom.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Please note any correspondence following application will be sent via trac.jobs &amp; the Trust&#39;s Resourcing Team**&lt;/p&gt;
